yeutter repeat retali threat on ec oil tax u.s. trade repr clayton yeutter said the unit state will retali if the european commun adopt a propo tax on veget oil , but he did not say what ec product would be singled-out for repri . speak to the nation grain and feed associ ( ngfa ) convent here , yeutter said he is `` cautiou optimist `` the controversi oil tax propo will be reject by the ec council of minist . yeutter said the propo tax is a `` flagrant violat of the spirit of gatt `` becau it would imperil the zero bind duti on u.s. export of soybean to europ . he said the reagan administr ha yet to decid on a retali list . the administr would not reveal a retali list unless the ec approv the propo , he said .